Here is a simple way to combine the elements in a list into one string:

```python
def join_strings(input_list):
    return ''.join(input_list)
```

This function uses the `''.join()` method which concatenates all the items of its iterable (in this case, our input list) and returns a single string. Note that if any item in your list contains leading or trailing whitespaces, they will be preserved when joining them together.

